From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 11:36:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm: k3: Fix SPL reserved-memory fixup order

AM65x SPL runs fdtdec_setup() and dm_init_and_scan() from
spl_early_init() before enable_caches() is reached.

When reserved-memory fixups are deferred until enable_caches(), they
rewrite the live control FDT after driver model has already bound
devices against it. On IOT2050 this leaves Cadence QSPI with stale DT
references, so SPI boot loses the flash child node and fails on bus 0.

Run the SPL reserved-memory fixups from fdtdec_board_setup() instead.
That hook executes after the control DTB is prepared but before driver
model scans it, so DM sees the updated tree from the start.

Build fdtdec_board_setup() regardless of DFU/USB_STORAGE so SPL fixups
always run. Keep the USB-specific fixup itself conditional.

Also match existing reserved-memory carveouts by configured load
address when applying TFA/OP-TEE fixups. Boards like IOT2050 may use a
board-specific node name (for example secure-ddr@...) instead of
optee@..., so address-based matching avoids leaving stale names that
later lookups miss.

Only apply reserved-memory fixups when the configured TFA/OP-TEE load
address is in DDR. On AM65x, TFA can reside in MSMC SRAM at 0x70000000.
Creating a no-map reserved-memory node for that non-DRAM address causes
Linux mmio-sram to fail probing and breaks icssg-prueth SRAM pool
allocation.

Keep the previous fail-open behavior in SPL by logging fixup errors
instead of aborting early. This avoids turning existing non-fatal DT
issues into a boot regression while still fixing the ordering bug.

enable_caches() still performs the fixups for non-SPL builds.

Signed-off-by: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-k3/am65x/am654_init.c | 20 +++++++++++++++++++-
 arch/arm/mach-k3/common.c           | 10 ++++++----
 arch/arm/mach-k3/common_fdt.c       | 30 ++++++++++++++++++++----------
 3 files changed, 46 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-k3/am65x/am654_init.c b/arch/arm/mach-k3/am65x/am654_init.c
index a4f038029d7c..7590b1f96139 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-k3/am65x/am654_init.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-k3/am65x/am654_init.c
@@ -17,6 +17,7 @@
 #include <dm/pinctrl.h>
 #include <linux/soc/ti/ti_sci_protocol.h>
 #include <log.h>
+#include <mach/k3-common-fdt.h>
 #include <mmc.h>
 #include <stdlib.h>
 
@@ -142,11 +143,28 @@ static int fixup_usb_boot(void)
 	return 0;
 }
 
+#else
+
+static int fixup_usb_boot(void)
+{
+	return 0;
+}
+
+#endif
+
 int fdtdec_board_setup(const void *fdt_blob)
 {
+	int ret;
+
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_SPL_BUILD)) {
+		ret = fdt_fixup_reserved((void *)fdt_blob);
+		if (ret)
+			printf("%s: Failed to perform reserved-memory fixups (%s)\n",
+			       __func__, fdt_strerror(ret));
+	}
+
 	return fixup_usb_boot();
 }
-#endif
 
 static void setup_am654_navss_northbridge(void)
 {
diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-k3/common.c b/arch/arm/mach-k3/common.c
index 19a6e24f38b2..56df43fe90a7 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-k3/common.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-k3/common.c
@@ -273,10 +273,12 @@ void enable_caches(void)
 	if (ret)
 		debug("%s: Failed to setup dram banks\n", __func__);
 
-	ret = fdt_fixup_reserved(fdt);
-	if (ret)
-		printf("%s: Failed to perform reserved-memory fixups (%s)\n",
-		       __func__, fdt_strerror(ret));
+	if (!IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_SPL_BUILD)) {
+		ret = fdt_fixup_reserved(fdt);
+		if (ret)
+			printf("%s: Failed to perform reserved-memory fixups (%s)\n",
+			       __func__, fdt_strerror(ret));
+	}
 
 	mmu_setup();
 
diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-k3/common_fdt.c b/arch/arm/mach-k3/common_fdt.c
index 39cb00c3f439..9f5849525aed 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-k3/common_fdt.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-k3/common_fdt.c
@@ -134,18 +134,23 @@ static int fdt_fixup_reserved_memory(void *blob, const char *name,
 		const char *node_name;
 		fdt_addr_t addr;
 		fdt_size_t size;
+		bool name_match;
 
 		/* Name matching */
 		node_name = fdt_get_name(blob, subnode, NULL);
 		if (!name)
 			return -EINVAL;
-		if (!strncmp(node_name, name, strlen(name))) {
-			/* Read out old size first */
-			addr = fdtdec_get_addr_size_auto_parent(
-				blob, nodeoffset, subnode, "reg", 0, &size,
-				false);
-			if (addr == FDT_ADDR_T_NONE)
-				return -EINVAL;
+		name_match = !strncmp(node_name, name, strlen(name));
+
+		/* Read carveout address/size once for both name and address matching */
+		addr = fdtdec_get_addr_size_auto_parent(blob, nodeoffset, subnode,
+						      "reg", 0, &size, false);
+		if (name_match && addr == FDT_ADDR_T_NONE)
+			return -EINVAL;
+		if (addr == FDT_ADDR_T_NONE)
+			continue;
+
+		if (name_match || addr == new_address) {
 			new_size = size;
 
 			/* Delete node */
@@ -168,12 +173,17 @@ int fdt_fixup_reserved(void *blob)
 {
 	int ret;
 
-	ret = fdt_fixup_reserved_memory(blob, "tfa", CONFIG_K3_ATF_LOAD_ADDR,
-					CONFIG_K3_ATF_RESERVED_SIZE);
-	if (ret)
-		return ret;
+	if (CONFIG_K3_ATF_LOAD_ADDR >= CFG_SYS_SDRAM_BASE) {
+		ret = fdt_fixup_reserved_memory(blob, "tfa", CONFIG_K3_ATF_LOAD_ADDR,
+						CONFIG_K3_ATF_RESERVED_SIZE);
+		if (ret)
+			return ret;
+	}
+
+	if (CONFIG_K3_OPTEE_LOAD_ADDR >= CFG_SYS_SDRAM_BASE)
+		return fdt_fixup_reserved_memory(blob, "optee",
+						 CONFIG_K3_OPTEE_LOAD_ADDR,
+						 CONFIG_K3_OPTEE_RESERVED_SIZE);
 
-	return fdt_fixup_reserved_memory(blob, "optee",
-					 CONFIG_K3_OPTEE_LOAD_ADDR,
-					 CONFIG_K3_OPTEE_RESERVED_SIZE);
+	return 0;
 }
